title: Head Teaching Assistant
description: HTA for Introduction to Software Engineering at Brown University (CSCI 0320). Carefully selected a staff of 20 undergraduate TAs for Spring 2023. Responsibilites include training the staff, assisting with grading rubrics, and leading course development.

title: MediCircle Website Intern
description: Designed vector components and proposed what is now the current website layout. Pushed towards a cohesive brand identity suitable for their age demographic.

title: Undergraduate Teaching Assistant
description: UTA for Program Design with Data Structures and Algorithms at Brown University (CSCI0200). Held 4 hours of TA hours a week for a class of over 400 students and served as a mentor during partner projects. Revised course material to incorporate ReasonML into assignments. Incoming UTA for Software Engineering (CSCI0320) in Fall 2022.

title: Demo Day First-Place Winner
description: Served as a mentee in a semester-long workshop that culminates in competitive pitches. Won first-place and secured seed funding for the proposal of a roommate cohabitation app to improve finding alone time in dorms.

title: Freelance Graphic Designer
description: Utilized proficiency in Photoshop and Illustrator to help local businesses modernize their brand. Jobs included designing custom iMessage stickers for boutiques to send to customers. On my own time, I designed 15 Snapchat community filters which are now active in places like Florence, Italy and Puerto Vallarta, Mexico. My filters have accumulated 32.2 million views total and 532K uses.

title: Salesperson at Romantiques
description: Learned to assist customers and actively work to maintain relationships with frequent customers. I contributed my graphic design skills by creating a set of gifs and stickers personalized for the store which included cartoonized versions of their best-selling products.
